history.content: Feel free to contact Instructional Support for future concerns of this nature, sorry we can't help much on here! http://inst.eecs.berkeley.edu/

Hello,

I'm not sure if this is the correct place to ask about this, but I've been having trouble logging into the machines in the Soda labs. I have 3 different EE/CS instructional accounts and I've activated all of them, and I could not log into any of them in Soda 330 or a couple different rooms on the second floor.

However, I can SSH into the Hive machines just fine, but attempts to log into the physical machines fail.

I was also with a friend today and she couldn't log into her account in 330 either.

I've never had this issue in previous semesters-- is there a new policy affecting attempts to log in while not during a lab time, or the machines block certain accounts at certain times or something?

Anyone else experiencing similar issues?
history.subject: Trouble Logging into Soda Lab Machines
